content:
When an Apex class that’s declared using the with sharing keyword launches an autolaunched flow that runs in the default context, the flow runs in system context with sharing rules. This update enforces this behavior starting from Spring ’24.

This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

Salesforce enforces this update in Winter ’25. The major release upgrade date for your instance can be found on the Trust Status page under the maintenance tab.

The flow runs more securely in the default context when an Apex class that’s declared using the with sharing keyword launches an autolaunched flow. Data access is restricted to the sharing rules of the user that executed the Apex class.

Data access is restricted for autolaunched flows run in the default context and launched by an Apex class. A query can return fewer rows than it did in system context without sharing, and an operation may fail because the user doesn’t have the correct permissions.
title: Enforce Sharing Rules for Autolaunched Flows
